  "prompt": "I'm 4 years into my H1B, my GC is not yet started. If I apply GC through consulting company, do I need to join this company before filing I-140/I485?",
  "response": "Here's some key guidance:\n\n1. Job Offer Requirement:\n- To file PERM/I-140, you need a valid job offer from the sponsoring employer\n- The employer must intend to employ you permanently in the position described in the PERM application\n\n2. Consulting Company Scenarios:\n- You typically need to join/be on the payroll of the consulting company before or during I-140/I-485 filing\n- The consulting company must demonstrate they have a genuine job opportunity for you\n\n3. Recommended Steps:\n- Get an offer letter from the consulting company\n- Ensure the job description matches your qualifications\n- Join the company's payroll before or during PERM/I-140 filing\n- Maintain documentation of the job offer and employment\n\n4. Additional Considerations:\n- Consulting companies often sponsor GCs for specific client project roles\n- Ensure the job description is detailed and matches your actual work\n- Maintain compliance with immigration regulations\n\n5. Consultation Recommendation:\n- Consult an immigration attorney for personalized advice\n- They can review your specific situation and provide tailored guidance\n\nNote: Each case is unique, so professional legal advice is crucial.",
